Pronunciation:
Notes: (J- or K-Force) ca1951 F.M. O'Brien, In J- or K-force yakker, a fool, clot; hence aj. hoony, foolish, dumb by Wellington tramwaymen e.g. Those hoony bastards will lose us our overtime. cf Gook
